2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed algorithm is a reinforcement learning algorithm, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
3. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper discusses decision making in a game engine, which can be analyzed using game theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm, which can be analyzed using control theory. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed algorithm can be applied to graphics in a role-playing game, such as path-finding.
